        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<a name="62822"></a>
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;08/25/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 05:14:39</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=781"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=781')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=62822&amp;TOPIC_ID=7515&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Cleric+pet+%2D+now+VI+went+overboard&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Clerics do NOT compete with other healers. I play in a raid guild and we need all heals we can get. Last time we had 4 clerics in VT to cover 50 guys and suddenly a cleric wanted to log and we had a huge discussion about going on or calling it a day.</P><P>If druids and shamans get better heals it is to the benefit of ALL and not a cleric nerf in any way. Therefore clerics<BR>a. don't need to bother about it<BR>b. don't need any compensation</P><P>EQ has become kinda weird anyways. We used to know necros as pure damage dealing class:</P><P><img src="http://home.arcor.de/neric/Xegony/EQ000319.JPG" border=0></P><P>Ok, I agree that was a bit insane back then, but look at us now!<BR>It is not even close to the past. Our best DoT takes over 1 min to do 2400 focused damage. Compare that to a wizard who can get critical nukes on Garrisons.....<BR>We get some utility crap like group friendly spells (WTF???). At least they managed to pass the role of the manabitch to the mages.</P><P>Classes used to have a definition and there used to be rules and restrictions, but ever since McQuaid got fired it all got washed up. <BR>If this goes on we will all end up as some sort of druid-bard with a pet. Sorry, but that is bull....</P><P>Warriors have tank and shall not cast!<BR>Clerics have to heal and don't need pets!<BR>Necros should deal damage and not be group friendly like druids!</P><P>N</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Neric Soulstalker on 08/25/2002  05:17:48<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

